enumDescriptions: Backfill job was never started for the stream object (stream has backfill strategy defined as manual or object was explicitly excluded from automatic backfill).
Backfill job will start pending available resources.
Backfill job stopped (next job run will start from beginning).
Backfill job failed (due to an error).
Backfill job failed since the table structure is currently unsupported for backfill.

description.description: A short description of the validation.

code.description: A custom code identifying this validation.

Validation.description: A validation to perform on a stream.

BackfillNoneStrategy.description: Backfill strategy to disable automatic backfill for the Stream's objects.

DestinationConfig.description: The configuration of the stream destination.

gcsDestinationConfig.description: A configuration for how data should be loaded to Cloud Storage.

destinationConnectionProfile.description: Required. Destination connection profile resource. Format: `projects/{project}/locations/{location}/connectionProfiles/{name}`

mysqlExcludedObjects.description: MySQL data source objects to avoid backfilling.

oracleExcludedObjects.description: Oracle data source objects to avoid backfilling.

postgresqlExcludedObjects.description: PostgreSQL data source objects to avoid backfilling.

BackfillAllStrategy.description: Backfill strategy to automatically backfill the Stream's objects. Specific objects can be excluded.

Empty.description: A generic empty message that you can re-use to avoid defining duplicated empty messages in your APIs. A typical example is to use it as the request or the response type of an API method. For instance: service Foo { rpc Bar(google.protobuf.Empty) returns (google.protobuf.Empty); }

StreamObject.description: A specific stream object (e.g a specific DB table).

errors.description: Output only. Active errors on the object.

sourceObject.description: The object identifier in the data source.

name.description: Output only. The object resource's name.

backfillJob.description: The latest backfill job that was initiated for the stream object.

createTime.description: Output only. The creation time of the object.

updateTime.description: Output only. The last update time of the object.

databaseService.description: Required. Database for the Oracle connection.

hostname.description: Required. Hostname for the Oracle connection.

password.description: Required. Password for the Oracle connection.

port.description: Port for the Oracle connection, default value is 1521.

username.description: Required. Username for the Oracle connection.

mysqlColumns.description: MySQL columns in the database. When unspecified as part of include/exclude objects, includes/excludes everything.

streamLargeObjects.description: Stream large object values. NOTE: This feature is currently experimental.

includeObjects.description: Oracle objects to include in the stream.

maxConcurrentCdcTasks.description: Maximum number of concurrent CDC tasks. The number should be non-negative. If not set (or set to 0), the system's default value is used.

excludeObjects.description: Oracle objects to exclude from the stream.

maxConcurrentBackfillTasks.description: Maximum number of concurrent backfill tasks. The number should be non-negative. If not set (or set to 0), the system's default value is used.

fileRotationInterval.description: The maximum duration for which new events are added before a file is closed and a new file is created. Values within the range of 15-60 seconds are allowed.

fileRotationMb.description: The maximum file size to be saved in the bucket.

path.description: Path inside the Cloud Storage bucket to write data to.

errorUuid.description: A unique identifier for this specific error, allowing it to be traced throughout the system in logs and API responses.

message.description: A message containing more information about the error that occurred.

reason.description: A title that explains the reason for the error.

errorTime.description: The time when the error occurred.

sourceObjectIdentifier.description: Required. The source object identifier which maps to the stream object.

LookupStreamObjectRequest.description: Request for looking up a specific stream object by its source object identifier.

ListPrivateConnectionsResponse.description: Response containing a list of private connection configurations.

nextPageToken.description: A token, which can be sent as `page_token` to retrieve the next page. If this field is omitted, there are no subsequent pages.

unreachable.description: Locations that could not be reached.

privateConnection.description: Required. A reference to a private connection resource. Format: `projects/{project}/locations/{location}/privateConnections/{name}`

cdcStrategy.description: Optional. The CDC strategy of the stream. If not set, the system's default value will be used.

RunStreamRequest.description: Request message for running a stream.

StopBackfillJobRequest.description: Request for manually stopping a running backfill job for a specific stream object.

Route.description: The route resource is the child of the private connection resource, used for defining a route for a private connection.

name.description: Output only. The resource's name.

createTime.description: Output only. The create time of the resource.

updateTime.description: Output only. The update time of the resource.

postgresqlColumns.description: PostgreSQL columns in the schema. When unspecified as part of include/exclude objects, includes/excludes everything.

operations.description: A list of operations that matches the specified filter in the request.

dataType.description: The MySQL data type. Full data types list can be found here: https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/data-types.html

nullable.description: Whether or not the column can accept a null value.

primaryKey.description: Whether or not the column represents a primary key.

ordinalPosition.description: The ordinal position of the column in the table.

oracleSchemas.description: Oracle schemas/databases in the database server.

validations.description: A list of validations (includes both executed as well as not executed validations).

NextAvailableStartPosition.description: CDC strategy to resume replication from the next available position in the source.
